ShiftedArgFunctionBase - class popt4jlib.ShiftedArgFunctionBase.
The class is a wrapper class for FunctionIntf objects, that evaluates the FunctionIntf object not on the actual VectorIntf or double[] argument x that it is given, but rather on a shifted vector x-, where the shift is passed in the params hashtable as a pair: <"function.shiftarg", double[] delta> However, if it is passed a non-vector of doubles argument, the eval() method simply passes along the argument to the underlying function without shifting it, since it does not know how to do the shifting.
